The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, August 30, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, August 30, 2003				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Create a splash at Calcutta Clubs monsoon programme featuring an artists workshop in the afternoon, followed by a musical programme.				 																Dance				 																																	Enjoy Sama-The Harmony of Life, a fusion of Manipuri, Odissi and Thang-ta, presented by Nandanik Manipuri Dance Academy, at Madhusudan Mancha, 6.30 pm.				 																Music				 																																	Tune in to the 31st annual meet of the Children Music Conference, at Khelat Memorial Hall, from 5 pm. Mayor Subrata Mukherjee to inaugurate.				 																																	Listen to monsoon ragas at Brishti Dharay Je Sur Baaje, at the Birla Academy auditorium, on Sunday, from 6.30 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Drop in at CIMA Gallery for the last day of Recent Works, from 2 pm to 7 pm.
